{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Its application areas are wide, such as image classification, image retrieval, image description, etc.",
    "Mokady et al. [17] first proposed a CLIP-based image captioning method by extracting image features from CLIP and using a mapping network to connect the two modalities of image and language.",
    "They only fine-tuned the mapping network and finally generated image captions from pre-trained GPT-2.",
    "However, this method only extracted visual feature information through CLIP and mapped it to the textual space without considering the intrinsic contextual semantic information of the image.",
    "As a result, the generated captions lack details."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Mokady et al. [17] first proposed a CLIP-based image captioning method by extracting image features from CLIP and using a mapping network to connect the two modalities of image and language."
  ]
